    "Details": "Developed by Majesty Metals and Manufacturing on Canopus IV, the Fer-de-Lance is a homegrown Canopian Star League-era BattleMech design. The Fer-de-Lance is a dedicated light scout mech and boasts a ground speed of 120 kph. The FDL-2E is a Star League-era upgrade of the design, armed with two each Medium Lasers and SRM-4s while a Beagle Active Probe offers some extra electronic support. A 240-rated XL engine provides the free weight for the warload. The Fer-de-Lance managed to survive the Succession Wars in decent numbers and remains a staple of the Magistracy Armed Forces.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
